\begin_inset Formula $x(r,\rho)$
\end_inset

 in a area of reference with a richness 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 depending on their characteristics 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 and the age 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 in the equilibrium - corresponding to differences in consumption habits
 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu$
\end_inset

 and assets 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta$
\end_inset

 as well.
 Further, since the new consumers entering and leaving the area of reference
 would imply a finite population growth (if at all), the assets within the
 reference would be exchanged among the young and poor consumers with the
 costs 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(r,t)$
\end_inset

 - corresponding to variation in accumulated assets across age 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 in the reference.
