[Choice of movement - and movement as an inferior good ] The choice between
 more consumption within the same reference and attempting to improve one's
 references through education are the fundamental choice that we are interested
 in the empirical analysis following the model.
 It is assumed that the urban settings in the economies offer an environment
 that is not matched in the rural environment - therefore, the choice to
 move up to an area of higher prosperity is always relevant throughout.
 With results from the cross-sectional analyses we present in Section 
